      • countOccurrences

        Map<Integer,Integer> countOccurrences(List<Integer> numbers)
        Returns a map containing number occurrences (mapping a number to the count of occurrences in a numbers list).

        Example: 

         Map<Integer, Integer> result = countOccurrences(Arrays.asList(1,2,3,3);

 result has the following mapping:
 1 -> 1
 2 -> 1
 3 -> 2
        Parameters:
        numbers -
        Returns:

      • createFilteredIntegerGenerator

        IntegerGenerator createFilteredIntegerGenerator(IntegerGenerator generator,
                                                NumberFilter filter)
        Returns a IntegerGenerator that decorates existing generator with filtering.

        The returned generator uses a passed-in generator as a source for numbers but returns only those which satisfy passed-in filter.

        Parameters:
        generator - generator.
        filter - filter.
        Returns:
        filtering generator.
        See Also:
        NumberFilter.accept(int)
